<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Written evidence submitted by Gosport Council</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence submitted by</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> Gosport Council</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">1.0</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Executive Summary</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">1.1</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">This Council is of the view that support, care or supervision elements of the exempt accommodation definition are met by the activities undertaken in the Council’s owned hostels</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> (used for statutory homeless placements)</span><a name="_GoBack"></a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">However, the exclusion of district councils within the exempt accommodation definition means that these hostels will not be exempt under Universal Credit (UC).</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">1.2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">This report for the Committee sets out:</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 45.97pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">he reasons why this Council wants to manage its ow</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">n homelessness persons hostels</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 45.97pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">he consequences to the Council’s Hostel Business Plans if district councils are not enabled to fall under exempt hostel definitions (but are instead considered under the homelessness subsidy provisions). </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 45.97pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">This Council </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">is asking for the review of exempt accommodation definition to not exclude councils from the said definition.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">2.0</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Background</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2.1</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Gosport Council has relied upon Council managed hostels to accommodate the statutory homeless for many years. However, all th</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">e hostel buildings were in need of disposal or refurbishment.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2.2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Gosport Council received Government approval to increase borrowing (Housing Revenue Account, HRA) to enable a new homeless person’s hostel to be developed in 2012. In addition, this Council</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s HRA is now committed to self- financing the refurbishment of one of the retained hostels. The total capital expenditure </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">for the newly developed hostel and refurbished hostel </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">in the region of £2 million.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2.3</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The total Council hostel capacity</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> after th</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">e 2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:super">nd</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> hostel is refurbished</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> will be 83 units of varying sizes. At present the Council has 67 units although 12 of these are part of the refurbishment plan. Even with this hostel capacity</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> a small number of households are currently being accommodated in Bed &amp; Breakfast (6 at 30/6/13).  The final refurbished hostel building will come on line in February 2014, giving the 83 unit capacity.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> The Council has its own in-house supporting people fun</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ded service for homeless households with a contracted capacity of 100, but at just over 1 hour </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">support </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">average per week.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2.4</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">From 1/4/14, 7 hostel units will be leased to a Supporting People funded scheme for 16/17 year olds and care leavers. This partner</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ship approach will address a strategic gap in accommodation with support provision for Gosport, our neighbouring Fareham Borough Council and Hampshire County Council Children’s Services. Both Hampshire Children’s Services and Hampshire Supporting People ar</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">e funding this </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">new service. The existing newly developed hostel (Agnew) is the only building where this young person</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s scheme could be delivered due to the existing supervision of that building. This new scheme has been a strategic priority since at least </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2003.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2.5</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">A further relevant fact is that 40 hostel units are </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">currently </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">occupied by residents with an assessed need for move on to supported accommodation</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The customer base of the Council owned hostels is in many ways no different from the customer base of the supported hostels in the district run by housing associations and voluntary agencies who would fall under the exempt hostel definition. The exclusion </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">of the Council owned and managed hostels there</span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">fore </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">appears both arbitrary and unfair. It could also undermine this districts strategic need to supplement Supporting People / other funded services by providing an emergency holding hostel pending vacancies a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">t these other hostels</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2.6</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Both the young person’s scheme outlined in 1.4 and the Council’s statutory homeless provision aim to:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 45.97pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">A</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">chieve a model of a place of change</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 45.97pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Provide accommodation that is safe and supervised;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 45.97pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Provide accommodation of a high stan</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">dard that is fit for purpose;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 45.97pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Provides accommodation that is managed by the Council.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The Governments HRA reform was intended to enable Council’s to develop accommodation and manage it. This has been achieved with the Councils current hostel strategy.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">3</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">0</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Universal credit Implications</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">3</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.1</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">A review of the Business Plans for the Council hostels has been undertaken and approved. There are some significant budgetary implications if the current definition of exempt accommodation remains. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">3.2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Current gross </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">occupation charges are around the £200 per week level. Upon migration to UC the LHA level plus an unknown management fee will be claimable in subsidy. For all but the households with an assessed 4 bed need, the rent level that can be achieved is markedly b</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">elow the £200 level. The following budget losses have been calculated and approved internally (these losses anticipate a management fee of (£40 per week).</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><ol type="a" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 86.46pt; padding-left:2.99pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Under 35 year olds</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">£119,068</span></li><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 86.46pt; padding-left:2.99pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">1 bed need cases</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">£50,635</span></li><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 85.78pt; padding-left:3.67pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2 bed need cases</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">£12,207</span></li><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 86.46pt; padding-left:2.99pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">3 bed need cases</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">£2,011</span></li><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 86.46pt; padding-left:2.99pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Total</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> budget loss</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">£183,923</span></li></ol></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">3.3</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The projected total budget loss of £183,923 compares to a total budget of £127,420 for out of office hours security; or £105,228 hostel staff budget (Supporting People staff budget is separate); or capital repayment </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">costs of nearly £158,000. As you can see, none of these budget areas can fully cover the projected budget loss. None of those budget areas could be tampered with without making the hostel unviable.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">3.4</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The above losses relate to the HRA hostels not being </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">exempt accommodation. In addition, rent award will be paid to claimants. Award may be paid to landlord after 4 weeks arrears and will after 8 weeks arrears. Although more difficult to project, budget losses could easily amount to a further £100,000. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">3.5</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Gosport Council’s temporary accommodation strategy places high importance to the Councils role in managing statutory homeless</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. One response to the changes upon migration to UC would be to try to get a housing association etcetera to take over the hostels. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Even if that were possible it would be an unwelcome forced change. That change also appears to be in opposition to the Governments strategy of enabling council’s (through HRA reform) to meet the challenges faced by them.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">27 September 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>